headline.main: FAST PLANES BOMB REICH RAIL SHOPS; Low-Flying Mosquitos Place Delayed-Action Explosives at Trier and Ehrang FIGHTERS OVER CONTINENT Five Missing After Attacks on Communications in Belgium, France and Germany

lead_paragraph: LONDON, April 1 (AP) -- The Royal Air Force celebrated its twenty-fifth anniversary today by attacking two towns in Western Germany. Startled Germans stood gaping in the streets at swift British Mosquito bombers, which dipped as low as fifty feet to plant their delayed-action explosives on industrial objectives.
abstract: RAF raids power stations and ry workshops, Trier and Ehrang; fighters attack French and Belgian targets; Ger rept on Rotterdam raid effect cited
